The paper discusses a network model for the evolution of social networks, which is a topic that falls under the scope of several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as it specifically deals with the study of social networks and their properties. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a possible category as the paper discusses a model for the evolution of networks, which could be relevant to software engineering. 
- cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) is another possible category as the paper deals with the study of social networks and their evolution. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper discusses a network model and its parameters. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a possible category as the paper discusses statistical estimators for the parameters of the model.
